   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Align the guide wheels for the horizontal carriage as needed.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_k5f_nz2_lcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <table id="table_sf3_nz2_lcc" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="43.43%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="43.13%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Lockout tagout</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To align the guide wheels, move the vertical carriage into the lower maintenance
               position.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Follow the instructions in Section 3 to position the vertical carriage.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Follow the instruction in Section 2 above to lockout-tagout-verify the power
                     to the lifting station is off.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Enter the safety fence area.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_i1x_4z2_lcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image placement="break"
                         href="media/image18.jpg"
                         align="center"
                         id="image_aqz_c1f_lcc"
                         scale="50"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Insert both safety bolts into the corresponding bores on the vertical carriage
               lifting mast, and fasten the fixing plate.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Always make sure that the safety bolts for the vertical carriage are properly
                     installed before carrying out work on or near the carriage.  </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="danger" id="note_wj5_f1f_lcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">An unsecured vertical carriage can  fall down  and cause serious injury or even
                     death. </p>
               </note>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_obq_g1f_lcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image placement="break"
                         href="media/image12.jpg"
                         align="center"
                         id="image_gg1_h1f_lcc"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Set an equal distance from the horizontal carriage to the horizontal guides.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Slightly loosen the lock nut.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Twist the bolt as needed. Make sure both the right and left wheels turn
                     evenly.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Re-tighten the lock nut.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_rhz_31f_lcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image placement="break"
                         href="media/image20.jpg"
                         align="center"
                         id="image_ryg_j1f_lcc"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To restart the lifting station </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the safety bolts.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove all tools and accessories.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure that all personnel have left the safety fence area and that the safety
                     fence doors are closed.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that all safety components are in place.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">When leaving the fenced area, press the Door Reset button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove LOTO and re-install the 3 circuit breakers in the MSK control
                     cabinet.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">At the control panel, cancel any faults by pressing the Reset Fault button on
                     the control panel.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Also, press the Reset Safety Fence Area button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure that no personnel are near the equipment, or in the safety fence
                     area.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Return the system to the Start position in Manual mode.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Then switch the system to Automatic mode. (For details, see SBS-OP-026
                     Operating the Lifting Station.)</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Observe the operation to ensure that the lifting station is working
                     properly.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="caution" id="note_zn1_k1f_lcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">There is a serious danger for anyone inside the safety fence area when the
                     lifting station is turned on.</p>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
